June comes with life updates. It’s been a month since we said our bittersweet farewell to Austin and moved to Reno NV! There are too many great memories to share from the past two years but here are some of my favorites. Sunshine, wildflowers, and new friends, I will miss this city always. Hopefully I will be back for visits! 

Ceramics has been on a pause during the move but life is settling in and production will start soon. What pieces do we want to see more of?
.
.

Being a ceramic artist means knowing when to let go of pieces when they just can’t be saved. I was so excited for this mushroom vase, but it cracked in the drying process and I couldn’t save it. Reno is SOOO dry and it has been a learning curve to work with the clay drying at such a rapid pace.

This clay will be recycled and made into something else soon, maybe another try at a mushroom. 
.
.
#mushroomart #ceramicart #learntoletgo #creepyart #aliciaanncermics #breakstuff

Dear 2023, thank you!! We all know that hard times come with the good times, but this year sure had SO MANY wonderful times and a whole lot of nature and ceramic eye balls.🥲
 
This year…

✨we moved from Austin TX to Reno NV and drove for 5 days in a 22’ moving truck. I miss you my ATX friends, I can’t wait to visit. 

✨Three if my best friends welcomed little ones into this world and I’m so happy to witness them take on motherhood, I have never felt more proud.

✨Paul and I were luky enough to witness two pairs of our friends say I DO. We love you!! 

✨OMG MY KILN WAS INSTALLED!! 
.
.
